attributes.additional_details:
Mandatory audio-visual recording would:
	•	Protect parties from unfair treatment and judicial errors;
	•	Provide a reliable record for appeals, complaints, and reviews;
	•	Strengthen transparency and public confidence in the justice system; and
	•	Support vulnerable and self-represented people in protecting their rights.

This reform would bring Scotland in line with other jurisdictions and could be implemented using existing Webex technology in the courts.
